        <td bgColor="black"><textarea cols="45" name="Message" rows="6" wrap="VIRTUAL">[quote]
Just in case some of you didn't know. I check out the description under dire charm yesterday...and i don't think it said this in the beginning. But it now says: 

"gives you a 'chance' to charm an NPC"

So...this CHANCE hits me as good and bad. Good in that ok, maybe this won't be taken away or nerfed hard once some nec's try to use it. Bad to me in that i'm thinking it's gonna have a 75-90% resist rate. Correct if i'm wrong, but i don't believe it said 'CHANCE' a little while back. 

But this seems maybe ok, as a balancing thing. I know every nec, chanter, and druid running around charming any 55 and below mob every 72mins with no resits....and having that forever will be WAY AGAINST THE FUCKING VISION...and they'll take it away. So maybe this chance....be it 10-25% chance to perma-charm something will still be good in raids/groups. If it resists, sure it sucks having to wait another 72mins for another try, but you're in a raid/group, so the mob shouldn't come kill you (hopefully). And with all the mobs that groups/raids fight...you should get lots of chances. Not to mention all the other necros, druids, chanters there will try to charm too.

But as far as soloing with dire charm....if it really is 10-25% success rate (i'm only guessing on this) Then...hmm..dunno, seems annoying having to try dire charm 5-10 times, before you get it. Cuz you fail, you have to then figure out how to not die ;))....then try again in 72mins. But then again, it is ungodly to think of having a lvl 55 hasted pet.

So just wondering your views on this. It all seems ok i suppose having to work up 27 AApts to get dire charm....then i'm sure it's gonna have a 10-25% or so success rate to further balance it out.

If this prevents it's nerf, then it's good. Cuz so many of us want the fun that dire charm will bring.  If 10-25% success rate....i'm gonna smack the shit out of any tank complaining if i get LUCKY enough to charm something, and i then have all this power with my new pet....That tank won't know the 27pts i went through for it, nor how often i'm sure this skill will fail.

Or maybe i'm being to pessimistic, maybe higher than 25%, dunno.

It also doesn't say "undead only NPC" heh, so who knows how that's gonna pan out

 
